rComments: Very organized, clear, and well explained prof

Does not care about his students. Expects students to learn material from one example, and no problem sets. His eyebrows are too thick. He is always in a bad mood. No one in this class enjoyed listening to his biterness.
Great prof.  Thorough, helpful and concise.  This guy's the kind of engineer I want to be when I graduate.
Great Dresser.  Very wise and la te da, if i do say so my self.
He hates students sleeping in class and not taking notes but doesn't mind eating and latecommers. Great prof. Explains material very clearly and concisely.

The course I loathed last year suddenly makes sense with Christopoulos. Very accomodating when you ask him a question. Clear and concise.  Might be a good idea to make notes next to his derivations. Makes a lot of sense when learned-you might forget later
